GOLDEN SPREAD PANHANDLE WIND RANCH, LLC MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF
1. Availability. Golden Spread Panhandle Wind Ranch, LLC (GSPWR) will make electric capacity, energy, and ancillary services available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales to any purchaser.
2. Applicability. This Rate Schedule is applicable to all market-based sales of capacity, energy, and ancillary services by GSPWR.
3. Rates. All sales shall be made at the rates established between GSPWR and the purchaser.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established between the purchaser and GSPWR.
5. Effective Date. This Rate Schedule shall become effective on the date specified by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
6. Compliance with Regulations of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. GSPWR shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning GSPWR’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes GSPWR to engage in affiliate sales under this Rate Schedule or otherwise restricts or limits GSPWR’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning GSPWR’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Rate Schedule.
7. Seller Category. GSPWR is a Category 2 Seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a), in the Southwest Power Pool Region, and a Category 1 Seller in all other regions.
8. Limitations, Exemptions, Waivers and Blanket Authorizations. GSPWR’s market-based rate authority is not subject to any limitations. GSPWR has been granted a waiver of the OATT and OASIS requirements of Order Nos. 888, 889 and 890, as well as section 35.28 and Parts 37 and 358 of the Commission’s regulations. Black Hills Power, Inc. et al., 135 FERC ¶ 61,058 (2011). GSPWR has also been granted the following waivers and authorizations: (i) waiver of subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission’s regulations, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of Parts 41, 101 and 141 of the Commission’s regulations, except sections 141.14 and 141.15; and (iii) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act and Part 34 of the Commission’s regulations to issue securities and assume obligations and liabilities. Golden Spread Panhandle Wind Ranch, LLC, Docket No. ER11-3401-000 (2011).
9. Ancillary Services: Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP.
Ancillary Services - Third Party Provider Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Frequency Response Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider’s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
